msContents.summary: Decameron, translated into French by Laurens de Premierfait.

supportDesc.extent: 658 leaves : 280 x 196 (215 x 130) mm. bound to 291 x 205 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, i (17th-century paper) + 658 + i (17th-century paper); [1-658]; modern foliation in pencil, upper right recto.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a Gothic cursive script.

decoDesc.decoNote: 4-line initial with foliate ornamentation in blue, gold, and pink (f. 1r); red initials and capitals.

history.provenance: Formerly owned by James P. R. Lyell (Zacour-Hirsch).
